cs.IT, cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.LG. 

The paper proposes a method for sparse representation of bivariate functions, specifically natural images. This involves finding a path in the domain of the function and applying a one dimensional wavelet transform. The paper also discusses encoding a Region of Interest in the image with different quality than the rest of the image. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory) which deals with signal processing and compression. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper deals with image representation. cs.MM (Multiscale and Multiphysics Modeling) is relevant as the paper proposes a multiscale transform. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are less likely but still possible as the paper discusses encoding a Region of Interest and finding a path in a deterministic way.
